                                    <watches>3</watches>
                                                                            <comments>
                            <comment id="35883" author="pjones" created="Mon, 30 Apr 2012 11:56:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Believed to be a duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1092&quot; title=&quot;NULL pointer dereference in filter_export_stats_init()&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1092&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1092&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="28504" author="nedbass" created="Mon, 13 Feb 2012 13:29:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;We are still trying to understand what happened, but it&apos;s hard to identify the clients because the UUIDS are all @&amp;lt;unknown&amp;gt;.  It could be that they were BGP nodes that get rebooted between jobs.  We suspect RPC traffic was not moving through the system well, but we don&apos;t know if it was due to high server load or some network or LNET router issue.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="28417" author="green" created="Fri, 10 Feb 2012 21:55:22 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The disconnect stale client message is about clients that failed to contact the server during the recovery window.&lt;br/&gt;
Were they dead or is there some other problem at play?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
